Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @sweet potato{3} lengthways and pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Rub the oil over the potatoes, then lay them, cut-side down, on the baking tray.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender and a knife slips in easily, ~{30-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1} as thinly as you can.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

Pop half the sliced onion into a #small bowl{} and add the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar for the pickle{1%tsp}. Add a pinch of salt, mix together and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the remaining red onion to the pan and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the mixed beans and @Worcester sauce{15%ml} to the pan. Allow the Worcester sauce to bubble away until evaporated, ~{30%seconds}, then stir in the @tomato passata{1}, @chipotle paste{20%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}.

Pour the @water for the sauce{100%ml} and @sugar for the sauce{1%tsp} into the pan and stir.

Bring the beans to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from the heat. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of water if it's little too thick.

Once the sweet potatoes are cooked, fluff up their insides using a #fork{} and add a knob of @?butter{} if you'd like.

Top with the Boston beans, @soured cream{75%g}, cheese and pickled onion (leave the pickle juice in the bowl, you need it for the dressing).

Mix the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing into the pickle juice.

Add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the bowl. Toss to coat, then serve alongside your jacky p.

Enjoy!